43491 #define NUM_UNICODE 21741
43492 
43498 int binarySearch(const char **strings, 
43499                  int start,            
43500                  int end,              
43501                  const char *find)     
43502 {
43503         unsigned int midpoint;
43504         int cmp;
43505         if (end < start) return -1;
43506         midpoint = ((end - start) / 2) + start;
43507         cmp = strcmp(strings[midpoint], find);
43508         if (cmp == 0)
43509                 return midpoint;
43510         else if (cmp > 0)
43511                 return binarySearch(strings, start, midpoint - 1, find);
43512         else if (cmp < 0)
43513                 return binarySearch(strings, midpoint + 1, end, find);
43514         return -1;
43515 }

43522 long convertNormativeNameToCodePoint(const char *name) 
43523 {
43524         int index = binarySearch(names, 0, NUM_UNICODE - 1, name);
43525         if (index < 0) {
43526                 fprintf(stderr, "Invalid Unicode normative name.\n");
43527                 return -1;
43528         }
43529         else
43530                 return codepoints[index];
43531 }

43539 unsigned int convertCodePointToUTF8(long codepoint, 
43540                                     char *out)      
43541 {
43542         /* Out of range */
43543         if (codepoint > 0x10FFFF) {
43544                 fprintf(stderr, "Invalid Unicode code point.\n");
43545                 return 0;
43546         }
43547         /* U+010000 to U+10FFFF  */
43548         else if (codepoint >= 0x010000) {
43549                 char x1 = codepoint & 0x003F;
43550                 char x2 = (codepoint & 0x00C0) >> 6;
43551                 char y1 = (codepoint & 0x0F00) >> 8;
43552                 char y2 = (codepoint & 0xF000) >> 12;
43553                 char z1 = (codepoint & 0x30000) >> 16;
43554                 char z2 = (codepoint & 0x1C0000) >> 18;
43555                 out[0] = 0xF0 | z2;
43556                 out[1] = 0x80 | (z1 << 4) | y2;
43557                 out[2] = 0x80 | (y1 << 2) | x2;
43558                 out[3] = 0x80 | x1;
43559                 return 4;
43560         }
43561         /* U+0800 to U+FFFF  */
43562         else if (codepoint >= 0x0800) {
43563                 char x1 = codepoint & 0x003F;
43564                 char x2 = (codepoint & 0x00C0) >> 6;
43565                 char y1 = (codepoint & 0x0F00) >> 8;
43566                 char y2 = (codepoint & 0xF000) >> 12;
43567                 out[0] = 0xE0 | y2;
43568                 out[1] = 0x80 | (y1 << 2) | x2;
43569                 out[2] = 0x80 | x1;
43570                 return 3;
43571         }
43572         /* U+0080 to U+07FF  */
43573         else if (codepoint & 0x0080) {
43574                 char x1 = codepoint & 0x3F;
43575                 char x2 = (codepoint & 0x00C0) >> 6;
43576                 char y = (codepoint & 0x0700) >> 8;
43577                 out[0] = 0xC0 | (y << 2) | x2;
43578                 out[1] =  0x80 | x1;
43579                 return 2;
43580         }
43581         /* U+0080 to U+07FF  */
43582         else {
43583                 out[0] = (char)codepoint;
43584                 return 1;
43585         }
43586 }
